          </div>

          <!-- Knee -->
          <div class="tab-panel active" id="tab-knee">
            <div class="condition-card">
              <div class="condition-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-exclamation"></i></div>
              <h4>Knee Osteoarthritis</h4>
              <p>Grade 1–3 cartilage degeneration causing pain, swelling, and morning stiffness. Treated with viscosupplementation, PRP, and targeted physiotherapy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="condition-card">
              <div class="condition-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-half-stroke"></i></div>
              <h4>Meniscal Tears</h4>
              <p>Degenerative or traumatic tears causing locking, clicking, and pain. Conservative management with injections and rehab avoids surgery in most cases.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="condition-card">
              <div class="condition-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-bolt"></i></div>
              <h4>Patellofemoral Pain</h4>
              <p>Pain around the kneecap worsened by stairs, squatting, or prolonged sitting. Managed through targeted physiotherapy, taping, and injection therapy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="condition-card">
              <div class="condition-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-compress"></i></div>
              <h4>Plica Syndrome</h4>
              <p>Irritation of the synovial folds inside the knee causing clicking and medial knee pain. Responds well to corticosteroid injection and activity modification.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Hip -->
          <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-hip">
            <div class="condition-card">
              <div class="condition-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-exclamation"></i></div>
              <h4>Hip Osteoarthritis</h4>
              <p>Groin pain, stiffness, and reduced hip rotation due to cartilage wear. Treated with viscosupplementation, PRP, and targeted physiotherapy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="condition-card">
              <div class="condition-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-ring"></i></div>
              <h4>Labral Tears</h4>
              <p>Tears in the cartilage ring surrounding the hip socket causing deep groin pain and clicking. Conservative management with injections and rehab.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="condition-card">
              <div class="condition-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrows-to-dot"></i></div>
              <h4>Femoroacetabular Impingement</h4>
              <p>Abnormal contact between the femoral head and acetabulum causing hip pain and labral tears. Managed with activity modification, injections, and physiotherapy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="condition-card">
              <div class="condition-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-fire"></i></div>
              <h4>Greater Trochanteric Bursitis</h4>
              <p>Inflammation of the bursa on the outer hip causing lateral hip pain. Highly responsive to targeted steroid injection with lasting relief.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Spine -->
          <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-spine">
