              <h4>Spinal Stenosis</h4>
              <p>Narrowing of the spinal canal compressing nerves — causing leg pain, numbness, and difficulty walking. Managed with epidural injections and physiotherapy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="condition-card">
              <div class="condition-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-layer-group"></i></div>
              <h4>Facet Joint Arthritis</h4>
              <p>Degeneration of the small joints connecting spinal vertebrae — causing central back pain worsened by extension. Treated with facet joint injections.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="condition-card">
              <div class="condition-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-hourglass-half"></i></div>
              <h4>Spondylosis</h4>
              <p>Age-related degeneration of the spine with osteophyte formation and disc narrowing. Conservative management with injections and core rehabilitation.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="condition-card">
              <div class="condition-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-exclamation"></i></div>
              <h4>Sacroiliac Joint Pain</h4>
              <p>Pain in the lower back and buttock from the SI joint. Often misdiagnosed as disc disease. Treated with targeted SI joint injections for rapid relief.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
