      <!-- Treatment Approach -->
      <div class="content-section">
        <div class="content-label">How We Treat</div>
        <h2 class="content-h2">Our <em>Treatment Approach</em></h2>
        <p class="content-p">Each patient receives a tailored combination of the following interventions — selected based on the specific joint, condition severity, and individual lifestyle demands.</p>

        <div class="approach-grid">
          <div class="approach-card">
            <div class="approach-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-syringe"></i></div>
            <div>
              <div class="approach-tag">Regenerative</div>
              <h3>PRP & Viscosupplementation</h3>
              <p>Platelet-Rich Plasma injections stimulate cartilage repair and reduce inflammation. Hyaluronic Acid injections restore joint lubrication. Both are derived from <strong>natural, biocompatible substances</strong> — no synthetic drugs, no systemic side effects. Used for knee and hip arthritis, meniscal degeneration, and labral pathology.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="approach-card">
            <div class="approach-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-bolt"></i></div>
            <div>
              <div class="approach-tag">Interventional</div>
              <h3>Targeted Joint & Nerve Injections</h3>
              <p>Corticosteroid injections directly into the affected joint or around compressed nerves <strong>rapidly reduce inflammation</strong> and provide significant pain relief. Facet joint blocks, SI joint injections, and epidural steroids address spinal pain sources precisely — without affecting the whole body.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="approach-card">
            <div class="approach-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-person-walking"></i></div>
            <div>
              <div class="approach-tag">Rehabilitation</div>
              <h3>Physiotherapy & Posture Correction</h3>
              <p>Strengthening the muscles around a degenerated joint <strong>offloads stress from the cartilage</strong> and slows further damage. Dr. Sarish Sharma coordinates personalised physiotherapy programmes targeting hip stabilisers, quadriceps, core, and postural muscles — addressing root causes, not just symptoms.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="approach-card">
            <div class="approach-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-leaf"></i></div>
            <div>
              <div class="approach-tag">Lifestyle</div>
              <h3>Weight, Nutrition & Activity Optimisation</h3>
              <p>Every kilogram of body weight places <strong>4–6 kilograms of force</strong> across the knee joint. Weight management, anti-inflammatory nutrition, activity modification, and appropriate footwear can dramatically slow arthritis progression — and are prescribed as part of every joint care plan.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Who this is for -->
      <div class="content-section">
