        <h2 class="content-h2">Is This <em>Right for You?</em></h2>
        <div class="check-list">
          <div class="check-item"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i><span>Patients with <strong>mild to moderate osteoarthritis</strong> of the knee, hip, or spine not yet requiring replacement</span></div>
          <div class="check-item"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i><span>Anyone with <strong>joint pain affecting daily activities</strong> — walking, climbing stairs, sitting, sleeping</span></div>
          <div class="check-item"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i><span>Patients who want to <strong>delay or avoid joint replacement surgery</strong> for as long as possible</span></div>
          <div class="check-item"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i><span>Individuals with <strong>labral tears, meniscal degeneration</strong>, or impingement not responding to basic physiotherapy</span></div>
          <div class="check-item"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i><span>Patients with <strong>spinal stenosis or facet arthritis</strong> causing chronic back pain and walking limitations</span></div>
          <div class="check-item"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i><span>Elderly or medically unfit patients who are <strong>not suitable candidates</strong> for major joint surgery</span></div>
        </div>
